   <documentation>
      <row>
         <Docu><![CDATA[= Action name =
PCK.AUTOMIC_VMWARE_VSPHERE.PUB.ACTION.NEW_VM_SNAPSHOT

= General description =
This action is used to create a new VM snapshot for the given VM. Filters such as folder path and location can be used to find the specific VM.
If more than one VM exists for the given VM name (and/or Folder path, Location) then it will create snapshot for each VM with the same name.
Once the action gets executed successfully, details of new snapshot(s) is printed in the Job Report. 


= Failure Conditions =
(none)

= Inputs =
* Server IP or DNS		: Specify IP address or DNS name of the vSphere server to which you want to connect. E.g. www.myvcenter.com
* Username	    		: Username which will be used for this connection. E.g. domain\username
* Password	    		: Password to your username.
* Port		    		: Specify port which will be used for connection. E.g. 8080
* Protocol	    		: Specify protocol you want to use for connection. E.g. https, http
* Virtual Machine Name		: Specify the virtual machines for which you want to create snapshot. E.g. myVM
* Location			: Specify vSphere container objects like ResourcePool, VApp, Host name, Folder, Cluster, Datacenter name where VM(s) are located. E.g. Testdatacenter
* Folder path			: Specify full folder path for the Virtual Machine. E.g. rootfolder/subfolder
* Snapshot Name			: Specify name for the snapshot. E.g. snap_1
* Description			: Provide description for the Snapshot.
* Overwrite Agent   		: Overwrites the default agent
* Overwrite Login   		: Overwrites the default login

= Behaviour =
(none)

=Return Value=
(none)

= Outputs =
* Return code is 0 in case of success.
* Return code is 1 in case of failure.

= Logging =
Logs will be displayed in the AE report.

= Example =
(none)
]]></Docu>
